entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: that makes sense tell me about your kids

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: my daughter she is five years old she will be starting elementary school next week and today is her birthday five years ago i had her she is very smart i taught her home i home schooled her for five years and she is adorable she is my heart

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: do you find it easy to be a parent

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: no this is like the hardest job ever

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what is the hardest thing about being a parent

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: it is very hard providing providing making sure that you wash their clothes cause cause i mean it is hard enough to be a parent but i am a young parent and i am a little more mature than her father so it is it is it is the providing part i would basically say making sure that you have everything that they need it is so complicated let alone it gives you enthusiasm to be more to go the extra mile even being here today i probably would have still been in bed but today is my daughter is party and i was trying to make whatever extra little money i could make you know to make sure that she has a good day so it is all about going the extra mile doing anything that you can do to provide to provide for them but it it is a very hard job

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: yeah what is the best thing about being a parent

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: that moment of the day when your child tells you how much they care about you and my daughter her favorite thing is to tell me i am her i am her heart you know and and how many i mean just call your name it just it is a sense of reality to be called mom or to call call dad and it it just like it infatuates you it also let you know like this is reality this is this is my life this is what i am living right now and it is a it is a very good feeling that is the best part of being a parent

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: that is so good to hear

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: thank you

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: okay tell me about an event or something that you wish you could erase from your memory

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: going through my mom passing away

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how did you feel in that moment

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i felt like i felt like basically that it was i felt kind of robbed in a sense like i felt everyone else had parents and i grew up with my grandparents and then for me to go so many years without actual you know mom and dad for me to get eighteen years old and then then she leaves me it was kind of like i do not know it was nerve wracking because i felt robbed you know it was like i did not have her all these years and then now that i am older and i am i do not even have her now so

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: yeah i am sorry tell me about the hardest decision you have ever had to make

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: signing the paper of having a c section when it was time for me to have my daughter i was so nervous so scared really did not know what to do how to take it and i mean like that was so scary

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what made you decide to do that

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: it was the safest way of bringing my daughter into this world

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: are you happy you did that

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: yes

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: that is good how easy is it for you to get a good night is sleep

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: it is hard i did not even sleep last night that is why i am yawning but i i kind of tend to try to do everything and i have to get back to that stage where i have to think about myself as well and give myself time

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what are you like when you do not sleep well

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: a little like this but actually i am a little nicer today just groggy

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: okay how have you been feeling lately

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: lately i have been feeling very confident about being positive about going the extra mile of being a good parent

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: that is great have you noticed any changes in your behavior or thoughts lately

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: yeah i actually really do not care what other people think anymore i used to let that bother me but i do not no more

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: have you ever been diagnosed with ptsd

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: no

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: have you been diagnosed with depression

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: no

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: tell me about the last time you felt really happy

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: today cause i was so happy that i brought my daughter into this world today on her birthday

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: h what would you say are some of your best qualities
